rComments: She is amazing. Very encouraging, yes sometimes disorganised but she takes your opinion into consideration and allows your voice to be part of the discussion. Down-to-earth and approachable.

I would never take a course with her again, she is very disorganized, there were times she didn't even show up for the lectures. For more than half the course I had no clue what she was trying to teach. She doesn't engage with her students very well.

Before the midterm it seemed to be rushed but somewhat organized, after the midterm I'm not sure what happened. There were times I wondered what the lectures were for. I wish she took more time with the material overall and was more engaging, it would have increased interest level and provided clarity.As a person she seems really nice though.

she is not really lecturing for the second half of the course and expect us to know it from reading the book. most material she covers are unclear. don't like the way she organize material. participation mark for the class are consisted of online,lecture,class participation which i don't know how she's gonna do this...
Her midterm's highly based on the book, but she seems like a nice prof.
She doesn't use online sources much, such as the blackboard. She only uses it to post notes but doesn't make other important announcements on it. She doesn't even seem like a professor.
Her assignments are unnecessary labour, such as cutting out 200 articles out of newspapers. She does not reply to e-mails. She is not very helpful even if you go talk to her personally.

Her assignments are unnecessary labour, such as cutting out 200 articles out of newspapers. She does not reply to e-mails. Her lecture slides are very disorganized, just like her lectures itself. She is not very helpful even if you go talk to her personally.

Rarely uses a mic in class, speaks very low that it's hard to hear her all the way at the back of the class. Sometimes her slides are in huge font and sometimes it's too small, which becomes a problem while printing or sitting far. She uses too many "ummm" and "uhhh" during lectures, which put students to sleep (thinks too often while lecturing).
